content: After someone on the AndroidGaming subreddit recommended Tile Snap, I noticed the developers name looked awfully familiar so I check and what do you know... it's the developer of Dissembler, one of my favorite puzzle games of all time. And then I noticed he also developed Boson X, one of the most underrated runners. This guy has a great track record and Jumpgrid is another great addition to his library. Gives some serious Super Hexagon vibes in it's simple art style and fast paced action.
Starts easy, but gets fiendishly hard
Simple concept, fast-paced challenging fun! Wish it was also available for older devices as my kids love it so much! Congrats on the Indiecade nomination.

Found this at indiecade and it was hands down one the most addicting game at the event. The levels are hard (in a good way) and the effects are really nice. The game also makes it really easy to keep on retrying (which makes it even more addictive). Also.. FIRST
